    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-09-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-09-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="267"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d267">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_VDH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Van Dyke</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d267fn1">The same to the Ambassador in Great
                        Britain, No. 2072, September 4.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 4, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>192. Department informed apples and similar American fruits must be consigned to
                    Netherlands Oversea Trust whereas fruits like oranges and lemons need not be so
                    consigned. Verify and if this discrimination exists, protest through most
                    effective channel.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
